        {
          "name": "The concentration in Slavic Studies requires students to complete a minimum of seven 1000-level courses devoted to the study of the East European civilizations: literature, history, culture, theater, political science, economics, international relations.  Typically, at least four of these courses will be from within the Department of Slavic Studies.  Students' choice of courses is subject to the approval of the concentration advisor.",
